# Task 1

**Lets get started!**

To check whether Vim is installed:

- Launch a Terminal Window

- Type "vim"

If you're looking at the Vim splash page

![https://i.redd.it/jxykk7sdrezy.png](https://i.redd.it/jxykk7sdrezy.png)

Then you're in luck!

Otherwise type:

**Debian-Based Distributions:**

sudo apt install vim

**Arch-Based Distributions:**

sudo pacman -S vim

**Fedora-Based Distributions:**

sudo dnf install vim-enhanced

**Windows:**

Go to:Â [https://www.vim.org/download.php#pc](https://www.vim.org/download.php#pc)

Download and install the "self-installing-executable"

Answer the questions below

Install Vim

No answer needed

Launch Vim

